com.kuka.geometry

Interface IObjectEventProvider

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ObjectEventProvider

    public interface IObjectEventProvider
    Provides methods for adding or removing listeners for the event model. It also supports firing property changed events.

      • addListener

        void addListener(Object listener)
        Adds any object as a listener.

        Methods of the listener object annotated with @Subscribe and an event as parameter are registered as handlers for events of the type specified by the parameter.

        It is mandatory to call removeListener(Object) to avoid memory leaks.

        Example application (also valid for background tasks) 

         public class SubscriptionExample extends RoboticsAPIApplication {
     @Inject
     private ISceneGraph sceneGraph;

     @Override
     public void initialize() {
         // register a listener on the desired object, e.g. on the scene graph
         sceneGraph.getWorld().getEventProvider().addListener(this);
     }

     @Override
     public void run() {
         // ...
     }

     @Override
     public void dispose() {
         // unregister the previously added listener
         sceneGraph.getWorld().getEventProvider().removeListener(this);
     }

     // use @subscribe annotation to mark methods for handling events
     // the type of the method argument determines the events the method handles
     @Subscribe
     public void handleEvents(ObjectStructureEvent event) {
         // ..
     }
 }
        Parameters:
        listener - the listener which should be notified
        See Also:
        TreeEvent

      • removeListener

        void removeListener(Object listener)
        Removes all registered listeners from the provided listener instance which were previously added.

        Casting into a special listener type does not prevent other listener instances to be removed.

        Parameters:
        listener - the listener to be removed
        See Also:
        addListener(IObjectStructureListener), addListener(IFrameStructureListener), addListener(IPropertyChangeListener), addListener(IPositionChangeListener)
